author: scheu
msg: The MessageTest unit test is a simulation of the flow for receiving a message and unmarshalling it.
It checks that certain constraints are met.
I added checks to make sure that the JAXBContext is cached, so that we don't
have expensive JAXBContext.newInstance() calls.  And the checks make sure the JAXBContext is properly
garbage collected (JAXBContexts can be absurdly large and lead to out of memory situations.)
The test changes validate that the current code is working correctly.
